==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unbody
<hw>Un*bod"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>body</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from the body; to
disembody.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her soul <qex>unbodied</qex> of the burdenous corse.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbody</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Unbody
<hw>Un*bod"y</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To leave the body; to be
disembodied; -- said of the soul or spirit.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unbolt</ent>⟦br⟧
